In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 2010 as Great Outdoors Month. He emphasizes the importance of protecting and enjoying America's outdoor spaces, which include national parks, local parks, farms, rivers, forests, and more. Obama launched the America's Great Outdoors Initiative to promote innovative strategies for conservation and to reconnect Americans with nature. This initiative also aligns with First Lady Michelle Obama's Let's Move campaign, which encourages children to lead healthier lives and be more active. Obama urges all Americans to visit the respective websites to learn more and join the efforts. He highlights that investing in natural places will create jobs in the tourism and recreation industries, while also preserving the country's heritage for future generations.